        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 12 at 4:27AM CDT by NWS Chicago IL</headline>
        <description>At 426 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking strong thunderstorms along
a line extending from 6 miles northwest of Rockton to near Rockford
to near Malta. Movement was northeast at 40 mph. Rockford Airport
recorded a 44 mph wind gust with these storms.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph.

SOURCE...Radar and observations.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Poplar Grove, Candlewick Lake, Kirkland, Kingston, Fairdale,
Caledonia, Harvard, Marengo, Genoa, Timberlane, Garden Prairie,
Chemung, Belvidere, Capron, Sharon, Cherry Valley, Sycamore, and
Loves Park.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
